Last Modified: 7/17/2020]
I have the 1957 edition of this book; fourth paperback printing. The games in the various editions seem to be the same, but the comments to the moves change among editions/printings! In 2003, Batsford published a revised edition with algebraic notation.

This book is one of the most popular and recommended chess books. The intended audience is beginners who have just learned the rules of chess but maybe not anything else. Chernev provides a comment on every move of every game!
https://worldchesshof.org/hof-inductee/irving-chernev
Some references on Irving Chernev...
Wikipedia
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Irving_Chernev
