{ -
After 8 opening moves the opening transposes into the Queen's Gambit Declined without Nc3; a variation where Black has fianchettoed his Queen's Bishop. Black takes advantage of a tempo White loses and opens the lines. Black's pieces are better placed. White loses a pawn but hopes for counterplay. However, when Black's Knight jumps to d4, White cannot take it because of a mate threat. White retreats his attacked Queen instead of trying for a Queen exchange. At that point the game is lost because Black's kingside attack is too strong. White makes a weak defensive attempt in 15.Bb2 and Black soon has a forced mate.

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salo_Flohr
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rudolf_Pitschak
- }
