1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bc4 Be7 4. c3 { White's goal is to secure a central formation which will allow him to lock-up the centre and proceed with a flank attack against Black's kingside without having to worry about a centre counter-attack. } 4... Nf6 5. d3 { Though the central pawn structures are symmetrical, White's lsb is better than Black's dsb which is boxed-in by his own pawns. This slight advantage is far from trivial. } 1-0


