Sometimes I play this chess program just to relax.
I play at blitz speed.
- }
1. d4 Nf6 2. e4? { Omega Gambit.
I'm not kidding; that is the name of this opening. :-) } 2... Nxe4 3. Qf3 Nf6 { I've got a pawn for a tempo and I expected White's Queen would have to move again. If ...d5 then I'd be moving the Knight anyway after 4.Nc3. } 4. h3 { Waste of time. } 4... d5 5. Bf4 c6 6. Qe3 { So the King Knight can develop to f3? } 6... Qb6 { Since the QB left the scene. } 7. b3 e6 8. Nc3?! { White has made holes at a3 and c3. The QN should not block the c-pawn. } 8... Qa5 9. O-O-O { Castling into an attack. I figured I'll castle kingside. } 9... Bb4 { Threatening to win the c3-Knight. } 10. Nge2 O-O { King safety before continuing to attack queenside. } 11. Qg3?? { Threatening to play 12.Bxb8 winning the exchange. But White has blundered. } 11... Nh5 { The White Queen is overworked. } { [%cal Ga5c3,Ge2c3,Gg3c3,Gg3f4,Gh5f4] } 12. Qf3 Nxf4 13. Kb1 (13. Qxf4 Bxc3 14. Nxc3 Qxc3 $19) (13. Nxf4 Bxc3 $19) 13... Nxe2 { Simplification since Black is ahead in material. } 14. Nxe2 Qa3 { Nailing the King down. } 15. Nc1 a5 { The attack plays itself. } 16. c3 Bd6 17. Bd3 a4 18. Qh5 { White threatens mate, but as Tarrasch once said, "Beginning of attack..." } 18... f5 { ... end of attack." } 19. g3?! { What? } 19... axb3 { Threatening ruin with ...bxa2+. } 20. axb3?? { Letting me find the mate. I knew to look because why else would the computer play such a silly move. :-)
White needs to protect a2 with Rd2 or Qe2. } 20... Qa1+ 21. Kc2 Ra2+ 22. Nxa2 Qxa2+ 23. Kc1 Ba3# { 0-1 Black wins by checkmate. } 0-1


