1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7 { The Orthodox defence. } 5. Nf3 h6 6. Bh4 O-O 7. e3 Ne4 { The Lasker Defence is meant to increase Black's freedom of movement through the exchange of a minor piece or two. } 8. Bxe7 Qxe7 9. Qc2 c6 10. Be2 Nd7 11. O-O Nxc3 12. Qxc3 dxc4 13. Bxc4 (13. Qxc4 { This is less recommended as it allows Black to form the e5 libertating-lever } 13... e5) 13... b6 { ...c5 was also possible but might seem premature - even though it isn't - so the text move follows the general rule "When in doubt, delay the lever". Here, Black prepares it by b6 which will also Black to fianchetto its QB. } 14. e4 Bb7 15. Rfe1 Rfc8 16. Rad1 a6 17. Bd3 (17. Bb3) 17... c5 18. d5 Nf8 19. Ne5 Qc7 20. Bc4 Rd8 21. dxe6 (21. a4) 21... fxe6 22. Bd3 Rac8 23. Bc2 b5 *


