{ We now come to queen and king against king. As the queen combines the power of the rook and the bishop, it is the easiest mate of of all and should always be accomplished in under ten moves. Take the shown position. A good way to begin is to make the first move with the Queen, trying to limit the Black King's mobility as much as possible. Thus: }
1. Qc6 Kd4 2. Kd2 { Already the Black King has only one available square. } 2... Ke5 3. Ke3 Kf5 4. Qd6 Kg5 (4... Kg4 { then } 5. Qg6+) 5. Qe6 Kh4 (5... Kh5 6. Kf4 { and mate next move. }) 6. Qg6 Kh3 7. Kf3 { King moves and Queen mates. } *


