[FEN "r2qkbnr/ppp2pp1/2np3p/4p3/2BPP1b1/2N2N2/PPP2PPP/R1BQK2R w KQkq - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ I shall now give a few positions or traps to be avoided in the opening, and in which beginners are often caught.

White plays: }
1. dxe5 Nxe5 { Black should have recaptured with the Pawn. } 2. Nxe5 Bxd1 3. Bxf7+ Ke7 4. Nd5# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } 1-0


