{ When three or more pawns are opposed to each other in some such position as the one shown, there is always the chance for one side or the other to obtain a passed pawn.

In the above position the way of obtaining a passed Pawn is to advance the centre Pawn. }
1. b6 axb6 (1... cxb6 2. a6) 2. c6 bxc6 3. a6 { and as in this case the White Pawn is nearer to Queen than any of the Black Pawns, White will win. } *


