[SetUp "1"]

{ The position of the Pawns does not permit White to draw by means of the actual or close opposition, hence he takes the distant opposition. }
1. Kh1! (1. Kf1 Kd2 2. Kf2 Kd3 { and White cannot continue to keep the lateral opposition essential to his safety, because of his own Pawn at f3. }) 1... Kd2 2. Kh2 Kd3 3. Kh3! Ke2 4. Kg2 Ke3 5. Kg3 Kd4 6. Kg4 { attacking the Pawn and forcing Black to play 6... Ke3 when he can go back to g3 as already shown, and always keep the opposition. } *


