{ In this position White with or without the move can win. Take the most difficult variation: }
1... Kh2 2. Ng4+ Kh1 3. Kf1 g5 4. Kf2 h2 5. Ne3 g4 6. Nf1 g3+ 7. Nxg3# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } { We can now see the different merits of the knight and bishop. Amateurs generally think that the knight is the more valuable piece of the two since, unlike the bishop, it can command both black and white squares. However, it is overlooked that it takes much longer to bring a knight from one wing to another. Also, a bishop can stalemate a knight; a compliment which the knight is unable to return. } 1-0


