1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 { This last move will incite White to build a pawn centre. } 4. c3 { Preparing d4. Black cannot let White have the centre and plans to destroy it with d5. } 4... Nf6 { In preparation of d5. } 5. d4 exd4 6. cxd4 { White now fully occupies the central squares, having exchanged a flank-pawn for Black's only centrally placed pawn. } 6... Bb4+ 7. Nc3 { White proceeds with his development, disregarding the coming attack against his pawn. He believes that any material loss will be mitigated by the general principle that the better developed player is advantaged by open lines. } 7... d5 { Black's attempt to destroy White's pawn centre. } 1-0


