8. exd5 Nxd5 { White has now lost his pawn centre and has an isolated d-pawn. Not only is this type of pawn unsupported by pawns on its flank, it provides a safe square to the opponent, just above it, and also serves to shield whatever enemy piece occupies it from a threat from a major piece. Black should buttress this d5 square. } *


