15. Qe2 Qd7 16. Rac1 c6 { Black is afraid White will sacrifice the exchange, leaving it with a Rook on the seventh rank and a second pawn for the exchange } (16... Kf7 17. Qxe7+ Qxe7 18. Rxe7+ Kxe7 19. Rxc7+ { Black would, however, have stood much better had such a scenario unfolded, because: 1- White doesn't have a passed pawn, 2- A knight is awkward against a Rook, 3- Black's King is very well placed for the endgame. }) 17. d5 cxd5 18. Nd4 { The tables are now completely turned. Not only has White gotten rid of its isolated d4 pawn, it now has a very powerful perch on the outpost square provided by Black's own isolated d-pawn! The e6-square now sticks out as a wonderful beachfront for the coming White invasion. } 18... Kf7 { White's only choice, under the circumstances, but it is too little, too late. } *


