1. d4 { [%eval 0.0] } { Notes by J. R. Capablanca } 1... d5 { [%eval 0.13] } 2. Nf3 { [%eval 0.05] } 2... e6 { [%eval 0.0] } 3. c4 { [%eval 0.0] } 3... Nf6 { [%eval 0.31] } 4. Bg5 { [%eval -0.09] } 4... Be7 { [%eval 0.01] } 5. e3 { [%eval 0.0] } 5... Nbd7 { [%eval 0.2] } 6. Nc3 { [%eval 0.25] } 6... O-O { [%eval 0.09] } 7. Rc1 { [%eval 0.0] } 7... b6 { [%eval 0.33] } 8. cxd5 { [%eval 0.46] } 8... exd5 { [%eval 0.45] } 9. Bb5 { [%eval 0.47] } { A new move
which has no merit outside of its novelty. I played it for the
first time against Teichmann in Berlin in 1913. The normal
move is Bd3, but Qa4 may the best, after all. } 9... Bb7 { [%eval 0.5] } 10. Qa4 { [%eval 0.13] } 10... a6 { [%eval 0.2] } { c5 at once is the proper continuation. } 11. Bxd7 { [%eval 0.2] } 11... Nxd7 { [%eval 0.13] } 12. Bxe7 { [%eval 0.01] } 12... Qxe7 { [%eval 0.23] } 13. Qb3 { [%eval -0.26] } { With the idea of preventing c5, but still better
would have been to castle. } 13... Qd6 { [%eval 0.23] } { Black could have played
c5. In the many complications arising from this move. I think,
Black would have come out all right. } 14. O-O { [%eval 0.19] } 14... Rfd8 { [%eval 0.29] } 15. Rfd1 { [%eval 0.13] } 15... Rab8 { [%eval 0.47] } 16. Ne1 { [%eval 0.11] } { The object was to draw the Knight away from the line
of the Bishop, which would soon be open, as it actually
occurred in the game. } 16... Nf6 { [%eval 0.38] } 17. Rc2 { [%eval 0.05] } 17... c5 { [%eval 0.39] } 18. dxc5 { [%eval 0.13] } 18... bxc5 { [%eval 0.15] } 19. Ne2 { [%eval -0.2] } 19... Ne4 { [%eval 0.27] } { All the attacks beginning either with Ng4 or d4 would have
failed. } 20. Qa3 { [%eval 0.19] } 20... Rbc8 { [%eval 0.22] } 21. Ng3 { [%eval 0.2] } 21... Nxg3 { [%eval 0.23] } 22. hxg3 { [%eval 0.13] } 22... Qb6 { [%eval 0.07] } 23. Rcd2 { [%eval 0.0] } { Rdc1
would not have been better, because of the rejoinder d4, etc. } 23... h6 { [%eval 0.0] } 24. Nf3 { [%eval 0.0] } 24... d4 { [%eval -0.1] } 25. exd4 { [%eval -0.13] } 25... Bxf3 { [%eval 0.0] } 26. Qxf3 { [%eval -0.1] } 26... Rxd4 { [%eval -0.05] } 27. Rc2 { [%eval 0.0] } 27... Rxd1+ { [%eval 0.0] } 28. Qxd1 { [%eval 0.05] } 28... Rd8 { [%eval 0.12] } 29. Qe2 { [%eval 0.12] } 29... Qd6 { [%eval 0.13] } 30. Kh2 { [%eval 0.0] } 30... Qd5 { [%eval 0.13] } 31. b3 { [%eval 0.0] } 31... Qf5 { [%eval 0.0] } 32. g4 { [%eval 0.0] } 32... Qg5 { [%eval 0.03] } 33. g3 { [%eval 0.13] } 33... Rd6?! { [%eval 0.65] } { Inaccuracy. a5 was best. } { Unquestionably the best move; with any other move Black would,
perhaps, have found it impossible to draw. } (33... a5 34. Qe4 g6 35. Qf4 Qxf4 36. gxf4 a4 37. bxa4 Rd4 38. a5 Rxf4 39. Kg3 Ra4 40. Rxc5) 34. Kg2 { [%eval 0.35] } 34... g6 { [%eval 0.0] } 35. Qc4 { [%eval 0.0] } 35... Re6?! { [%eval 0.82] } { Inaccuracy. Rd2 was best. } (35... Rd2 36. Rxd2 Qxd2 37. Qxa6 Kg7 38. Qa8 Qc2 39. Qa5 Qe4+ 40. Kf1 Qh1+ 41. Ke2 Qe4+ 42. Kd2) 36. Qxc5 { [%eval 0.85] } 36... Qxg4 { [%eval 0.8] } 37. f3 { [%eval 0.78] } 37... Qg5 { [%eval 0.75] } 38. Qxg5 { [%eval 0.56] } 38... hxg5 { [%eval 0.64] } 39. Kf2 { [%eval 0.5] } 39... Rd6 { [%eval 0.7] } 40. Ke3 { [%eval 0.65] } 40... Re6+ { [%eval 0.88] } 41. Kd4 { [%eval 0.84] } 41... Rd6+?! { [%eval 1.63] } { Inaccuracy. Kf8 was best. } (41... Kf8 42. Rc5) 42. Ke3?! { [%eval 0.83] } { Inaccuracy. Kc5 was best. } { K-c5 was too risky. The way to win was
not at all clear and I even thought that with that move Black
might win. } (42. Kc5 Re6 43. b4 f5 44. a4 Kf7 45. a5 Ke7 46. Rd2 Re5+ 47. Kb6 Rb5+ 48. Kxa6 Rxb4) 42... Re6+ { [%eval 0.87] } 43. Kf2 { [%eval 0.6] } 43... Rd6 { [%eval 0.49] } 44. g4 { [%eval 0.36] } 44... Rd1?! { [%eval 1.02] } { Inaccuracy. f5 was best. } (44... f5 45. Ke3 Kg7 46. Rc7+ Kh6 47. Rc4 Re6+ 48. Kd4 Rd6+ 49. Ke5 Rd2 50. a4 Rd3 51. gxf5) 45. Ke2 { [%eval 0.57] } { Ke3 was the
