1. d4 e6 2. e4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nd7 5. Nf3 Ngf6 6. Bd3 Be7 (6... Nxe4 7. Bxe4 Nf6 8. Bg5 Be7 9. Bxf6) 7. O-O Nxe4 8. Bxe4 Nf6 9. Bd3 b6 { Tactically premature, before castling, as White will demonstrate. } 10. Ne5 O-O (10... Bb7 11. Bb5+ { Preventing Black from castling }) 11. Nc6 Qd6 12. Qf3 Bd7 13. Nxe7+ Qxe7 14. Bg5 { Increasing the pressure on Black's castled King's position. } 14... Rac8 (14... h6 { Attempting to remove some pressure. }) 15. Rfe1 Rfe8 16. Qh3 Qd6 { White's advantage is now absolutely crushing and his attack is unstoppable. } (16... h6 17. Bxh6 gxh6 18. Qxh6 { And White has a crushing advantage and an unstoppable attack against Black's beleaguered King. }) 17. Bxf6 gxf6 18. Qh6 f5 19. Re3 Qxd4 20. c3 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


