1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 { Believing the old adage "The best defense is a good offense". } 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. d4 Be7 6. Bd3 Nf6 { With this series of moves, Black has chosen to ignore the fight for e4 which one usually finds with the Petroff. This concession will be put to immediate use by White whose greater mobility will sooner or later have great bearing on how the game unfolds. } 7. O-O O-O 8. h3 { Restricting Black's lsb's range, robbing it of the g4 square as well as preparing White kingside offensive. } 8... Be6 9. c4 { Further restricting Black's lsb's range, while establishing a strong pawn-centre and allowing Nc3 without restricting c4. } 9... c6 { better is 9...d5 10.c5 b6 11.Be3 Ne4 12.Nc3 Nxc3
13.bxc3 bxc5 = +0.37 (23 ply) } 10. Ng5 { Attacking Black's lsb and preparing f5 } 10... Na6 11. Nc3 { Developing the queenside Knight as well as providing White's lsb with a retreat to b1 should it come under attack } 11... Nc7 1-0


