4. e5 Nfd7 5. Nce2 { White wants to counter ...c5 with c3, attempting to keep the pawn chain intact rather than with f4 and remain the master of e5. } 5... c5 6. c3 Nc6 7. f4 cxd4 8. cxd4 Bb4+ 9. Bd2 Qb6 10. Nf3 { Planning to exchange Queens, therefore allowing Black to castle so his King will be unfavourable placed for the endgame. } 10... O-O 11. Bxb4 Qxb4+ 12. Qd2 Nb6 13. Nc3 Rd8 14. Nb5 { Intending Nd6, cutting-off the Black King's Rook. } 14... Bd7 15. Nd6 Rab8 16. Rc1 Qxd2+ 17. Kxd2 { The point of the exchange, which White took care not to initiate himself so his King could move towards the centre by capturing the Queen. } *


