21. b3 Nb4 22. a3 { Offering the Exchange, which Black declines. } 22... Nbc6 { Intending ...Na5-Nc4 } 23. b4 { Avoiding 24.Na4 which would have left Black much the better. } (23. Na4 Na5 24. Nc5 Rxc5 25. Rxc5 Nxb3+) 23... h6 24. h4 Nb8 25. Ke3 { Making room for the Knight. } 25... Rc7 26. Rc2 Rdc8 27. Rhc1 Kf8 28. g4 Be8 29. Nd2 Nd7 30. Nb3 Nb6 31. Nc5 { Winning the race. If Black goes for the Exchange, White will stand better once the dust has settled and if Black foregoes the Exchange, White will have blocked the c-file - thus making the Rooks on the c-file somewhat irrelevant - and allowing White to lauch a Kingside offensive. } 31... Nc4+ 32. Bxc4 dxc4 33. N5e4 { White's Knight now sits on an even better location that the previous perch he stood on. } 33... b5 34. Nd6 Rb8 35. f5 { White's careful preparations being over, the attack against Black's kingside is finally launched. } 35... Bd7 36. Rf2 Nd5+ 37. Nxd5 exd5 38. g5 h5 { White now has a significant advantage over Black. } *


