1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 { The "Berlin Defence". Black counterattacks rather than defending the e5 pawn. } 4. d3 { Steinitz, unlike Morphy, is not interested in opening-up the game: he wants to fix the centre in order to begin a kingside offensive. } 4... d6 { Protecting the e5 pawn but White now has the advantage of a Bishop unrestricted by his pawn chain. } 1-0


