4... d6 5. d3 Nf6 { Black rightly feels he is under no great rush to castle. } 6. Bg5 { White believes he has ably and powerfully developed his dsb as it pins Black's Nf6 to his Queen. } 6... h6 7. Bh4 g5 { White presumably now understand the predicament he has placed himself in by his tempestuous and overly aggressive play. Had he not castled, the situation would not be so dire. Had he simply settled for the excellent Be3, there would be no situation to speak of!
But Black has seized the opportunity, the protected and closed centre as well as the opponent's castled king literrally scream out for a pawn attack on the kingside! } *


