[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.12.15"]
[UTCTime "22:49:04"]

14. Nxe5 Nxe5 15. Be2 { White clearly leads in development and, as such, seeks to open up the game, a plan Black should strive to oppose by keeping in closed by controlling the key e5 square. } 15... f5 { White clearly leads in development and, as such, seeks to open up the game, a plan Black should strive to oppose by keeping in closed by controlling the key e5 square. Black's last move, however, shows his dangerous lack of positional understanding as it not only opens up the e-file as well as the a2-g8 diagonal his King sits on at g8 but also opens the a1-h8 long diagonal which can no longer be obtructed by f6. Morphy is now poised to become Master of these open lines. } 16. f4 Nc6 17. Bc4+ Kh8 18. Bb2 Qe7 19. Rde1 Rf6 20. exf5 Qf8 { White is now master of the open lines and, as is so often the can when in command of a superior position, a definitive tactical opportunity arises which Morphy pounces upon to bring his opponent to his knees. } *


