13. gxf3 Qg5+ 14. Kh1 Ne7 15. Ne2 { White reorganizes his forces to control the f4 square, pivotal to White's plan of attack } 15... Ng6 16. Rg1 Qf6 { Black happily obliges, relocating his Queen to f6 from where she can direct her powerful gaze on White's weak d4 pawn. } 17. Qd3 Kg8 { Preventing e5 and soon linking up Black's rooks via the ...h6, ...Kh7 sequence. } *


