[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/PixelatedParcel"]
[FEN "r6r/p1p1nppk/1bp2q1p/3p1P2/3PP3/3Q4/PB2NP1P/R5RK w - - 0 22"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.12.21"]
[UTCTime "16:48:28"]

22. f3 Rad8 23. Nf4 { The beginning of what will strike most reader's as a very forceful attack on Black's defensive position. } 23... Rhg8 24. Nh5 Qh4 25. f6 Qxh5 { Faced with a choice, Black's guiding principle is to follow the strategic imperatives dictated by the positional requirements of the board: the domination of the centre remains the key to Black's long-term chances of success and transient difficulties related to the defence of his position are simply viewed as a necessary price to pay to achieve the desired end. } 26. fxe7 Rd7 { Keeping his eye on the goal of centre domination by allowing for the eventual doubling of rooks along the d-file, rather than reflexively playing 26...Rde8 } 27. exd5+ g6 28. Rae1 Re8 { Black has now set the table for his own plans to dictate the course of the game. All that is required is careful defence until White has expended his bag of tricks. } *


