Stean, Michael. Simple Chess: New Algebraic Edition (Dover Chess) (p. 93). Dover Publications. Édition du Kindle. } 15... Rxb8 { [%eval -0.23] } 16. Ba7 { [%eval -0.29] } 16... Ra8 { [%eval -0.27] } 17. Bb6 { [%eval -0.33] } 17... Bb7 { [%eval -0.5] } 18. a3 { [%eval -0.31] } 18... Rfc8 { [%eval -0.4] } { Black has the half-open c file. He threatens …Bxa3, undermining the Knight. The Knight cannot move away because it is ‘pinned’ in front of the c Pawn. Half-open files do not need entry points. They naturally generate pressure.
