Stean, Michael. Simple Chess: New Algebraic Edition (Dover Chess) (p. 95). Dover Publications. Édition du Kindle. } 27. c4 { [%eval -1.49] } 27... bxc3 { [%eval -1.37] } 28. Rxc3 { [%eval -1.69] } 28... Nd5 { [%eval -1.49] } 29. Rxc6 { [%eval -1.37] } 29... Rxc6 { [%eval -1.47] } 30. Rb2 { [%eval -2.07] } 30... Bf6 { [%eval -1.99] } 31. Ra2 { [%eval -1.87] } 31... Rc8 { [%eval -1.75] } 32. Bd2?! { [%eval -2.35] } { Inaccuracy. Best move was b4. } (32. b4 Kg7) 32... Rb8 { [%eval -2.26] } 33. Nc1 { [%eval -2.21] } 33... Nb4 { [%eval -2.16] } 34. Bxb4 { [%eval -2.3] } 34... Rxb4 { [%eval -2.07] } 35. Rf2 { [%eval -2.16] } 35... Be7 { [%eval -2.0] } 36. Rf3 { [%eval -1.84] } 36... Bd6 { [%eval -1.71] } 37. Ne2 { [%eval -2.23] } 37... Re4 { [%eval -2.39] } 38. Rd3 { [%eval -2.2] } 38... Bc5 { [%eval -2.24] } 39. Rc3 { [%eval -2.39] } 39... Bf2 { [%eval -2.28] } 40. Rc2 { [%eval -2.25] } 40... Kg7 { [%eval -2.28] } 41. Ng1?! { [%eval -3.19] } { Inaccuracy. Best move was g4. } (41. g4 hxg3) 41... Rxf4 { [%eval -3.24] } 42. Nf3 { [%eval -3.13] } 42... Bg3 { [%eval -3.12] } 43. Kg1 { [%eval -3.36] } 43... Re4 { [%eval -3.24] } 44. Kf1 { [%eval -3.24] } 44... Re3 { [%eval -3.03] } 45. Rb2 { [%eval -3.08] } 45... e5 { [%eval -3.13] } 46. Rb1 { [%eval -3.0] } 46... e4 { [%eval -2.83] } { 0-1 White resigns. } { Black had a 4-3 majority on the King side (e, f, g, h Pawns, vs. f, g, h Pawns) and White a 3-2 surplus on the Queenside (c, b, a Pawns vs. b and a Pawns). This distribution is fundamentally favorable for Black,
