[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.11.25"]
[UTCTime "23:39:55"]

{ White has gambited a pawn to further the two chief aims of his opening, the King's gambit: 1- pressure on the f-file and 2- the formation of a pawn center.

Black defends the gambit pawn without delay by immediately playing 3...b5 but in doing so weakens the f6 and f5 squares.

The spirit of the opening calls for White to undermine the gambit pawn's defences in order to eliminate the f4 pawn and open the f-file. }
 *


