1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 { Though not a developing move, 3...exd4 is not a loss of tempo as White will eventually Nxd4.
In the Scotch game, Black usually aims for the removal of White's e4 pawn. White wants to prevent his opponent from opening the game too early with d5.
The fight therefore thematically revolves around the e4 and d5 squares. } *


