[Event "Anderssen-Paulsen (Vienna, 1873) Philidor's Defence: The isolated pawn: the weak square in front of it"]
[Date "2019.11.27"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Anderssen-Paulsen (Vienna, 1873) Philidor's Defence"]
[ChapterName "The isolated pawn: the weak square in front of it"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/9sPSMjuG/3zqGKint"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/PixelatedParcel"]
[FEN "8/pp3ppp/3p4/8/8/8/PPP2PPP/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.11.27"]
[UTCTime "04:46:31"]

{ By forcing Black to create an isolated pawn, White has created a long term weakness in the square in front of that pawn, since no neighboring pawns can support it.

As a consequence, that weak square will fall entirely under White's control who will seek to place a piece on it with great and lasting effect.

Black's isolated pawn will also provide shelter for whatever piece White chooses to post on the square in front of it. }
 *


