1... Qd7 2. a3 { Having secured a positional advantage, White improve's his King's position with a waiting move. } 2... Qf7 3. h3 { This move prepares a pawn assault against Black's kingside. This should only be attempted when the opponent has no chance of breaking through in the centre.
Black cannot respond with the usual g6-Bg7 defensive setup because if g6, then immediate ...Nf6+, hence the powerful placement of White's Knight on the d5 square. } 3... a6 { Securing the pawn from attack by the Queen, as Black's Rook is needed elsewhere. } { [%csl Ga6] } 4. g4 Re8 5. f4 Re6 6. g5 b5 7. h4 Re8 8. Qd3 Rb8 9. h5 a5 10. b4 axb4 11. axb4 Qxh5 12. Qxf5 Qf7 13. Qd3 Bd7 14. Ne4 Qf5 15. Rh1 Re8 16. Nef6+ gxf6 17. Nxf6+ Kf7 18. Rxh7+ Bg7 19. Rxg7+ Kxg7 20. Nxe8+ Kf8 21. Qxf5+ Bxf5 22. Nxd6 *


