{ This position arose after White had played 11.Bd2, in a Falkbeer Counter Gambit in which White focused on gaining and maintaining a material (pawn) advantage at the expense of his development. White captured a first pawn, then a second, which Black chose not to defend, prioritising his development and opening lines. }
 *


[Event "Rosanes-Anderssen (Breslau, 1862) Falkbeer Counter Gambit: The pawn structures after 11.Bd2"]
[Date "2019.11.25"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
