[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.11.25"]
[UTCTime "02:13:19"]

{ These are the respective pawn structures, after 11.Bd2
Black is down two pawns, has no central pawns, has an isolated c pawn and a pawn minority on the queenside.
One is tempted to think Black is in horrible trouble and must come up short in the endgame.
So, why would Black accept to be saddled with such a long-term material and structural disadvantage? }
 *


