[Event "Rosanes-Anderssen (Breslau, 1862) Falkbeer Counter Gambit: Black's plan is set in motion and quickly leads to mate"]
[Date "2019.11.25"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Rosanes-Anderssen (Breslau, 1862) Falkbeer Counter Gambit"]
[ChapterName "Black's plan is set in motion and quickly leads to mate"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/qGZ9ARWo/OjDgC6Ax"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/PixelatedParcel"]
[FEN "r1bqr1k1/p4ppp/2p2n2/2b5/4NP2/3P4/PPPBQ1PP/R3K1NR b KQ - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.11.25"]
[UTCTime "02:39:53"]

1... Nxe4 { Black puts his plan in motion } 2. dxe4 { Forced } 2... Bf5 { White's e-pawn is pinned to the misplaced White Queen, itself lying directly in front of her Regent, both at the opposite end of the half-open e-file on which sits the powerful Re8. Black's Bf4 lies is powerfully placed on the important h7-b1 diagonal. } 3. e5 { In attempting to secure his e-pawn by advancing it one square, White actually compounds his problem by giving Black's Bf5 a clear line of sight on the vulnerable c2 pawn. } 3... Qb6 { Black continues its development, forming a Queen-Bishop battery along the important a7-g1 diagonal, occupying the half-open b-file with a clear line of sight on the vulnerable b2 pawn and putting its Rooks in communication. } 4. O-O-O { White castle's Queenside, walking right into the Lion's open jaw. All that is left is to clench its powerful teeth around White's precarious defensive position and annihilate all chances of White escaping with his life. } 4... Bd4 5. c3 Rab8 6. b3 Red8 7. Nf3 Qxb3 8. axb3 Rxb3 9. Be1 Be3+ { White resigns. 0-1 } *


