1. d4 { [%eval 0.25] } 1... d5 { [%eval 0.25] } 2. Nc3 { [%eval -0.15] } 2... c5 { [%eval 0.06] } { D00 Queen's Pawn Opening: Veresov Attack, Irish Gambit } 3. e3 { [%eval -0.39] } { I am no chess erudite, but with this move White boxes in his dsb. } 3... e5?? { [%eval 1.47] } { Blunder. Best move was e6. } { (-0.39 → 1.48) Blunder. Best move was e6. } { Going for an unsustainably large pawn formation in the centre. } (3... e6 4. Nf3 a6 5. Bd3 c4 6. Be2 b5 7. e4 dxe4 8. Nxe4) 4. dxe5 { [%eval 1.28] } 4... d4 { [%eval 1.55] } 5. exd4 { [%eval 1.82] } 5... cxd4 { [%eval 1.57] } { Still not a single developing move from Black, after 5 moves each. } 6. Bb5+? { [%eval 1.12] } { (2.33 → 1.18) Mistake. Best move was Nb5. } (6. Nb5 Nc6) 6... Nc6 { [%eval 1.32] } 7. Nce2?? { [%eval -2.81] } { (1.26 → -3.27) Blunder. Best move was Bxc6+. } { Leaving himself wide-open to the tactical and common Qa5+, winning White's lsb and giving Black a game-winning advantage before the opening is even completed. } (7. Bxc6+ bxc6 8. Nce2 Qb6 9. Nf3 Bb4+ 10. Bd2 Bxd2+ 11. Qxd2 c5 12. c3 dxc3 13. bxc3 Ne7) 7... Qa5+ { [%eval -2.86] } 8. Bd2? { [%eval -4.61] } { Mistake. Best move was c3. } { (-3.12 → -4.50) Inaccuracy. Best move was c3. } (8. c3 Qxb5) 8... Qxb5 { [%eval -4.5] } { Black now has a crushing advantage. Safe and solid accompanying a simplification through exchange strategy almost guarantee the win for Black. } 9. Nf3 { [%eval -4.69] } 9... Be6?! { [%eval -3.25] } { (-4.71 → -3.55) Inaccuracy. Best move was Bg4. } (9... Bg4 10. O-O O-O-O 11. a4 Qd5 12. Ne1 Nxe5 13. Bf4 Nf6 14. Nd3 Bd6 15. f3 Bf5 16. Ng3) 10. O-O { [%eval -3.52] } 10... Nge7?! { [%eval -2.65] } { Inaccuracy. Best move was O-O-O. } { Black fails to force simplification and his overconcern with castling kingside loses the central pawn as well as the initiative. } (10... O-O-O) 11. Nexd4 { [%eval -2.82] } 11... Nxd4 { [%eval -2.66] } 12. Nxd4 { [%eval -2.83] } 12... Qxe5 { [%eval -2.79] } 13. Nxe6 { [%eval -2.85] } 13... Qxe6?! { [%eval -1.9] } { Inaccuracy. Best move was fxe6. } { (-3.00 → -2.01) Inaccuracy. Best move was fxe6. } { Black's position is now infinitely better than after 8...Qxb5 } (13... fxe6 14. Re1 Qf5 15. Qe2 (15. Bc3 Rd8 16. Qe2 Kf7 17. Rad1 Rxd1 18. Qxd1 Nd5 19. Re5 Qg6 20. Bd4) 15... O-O-O 16. a3 Nc6 17. Bc3 Bc5 18. Qxe6+ Qxe6 19. Rxe6 Bd4 20. Bxd4) 14. Re1 { [%eval -1.69] } 14... Qd6?! { [%eval -0.65] } { Inaccuracy. Best move was Qd7. } (14... Qd7 15. Qe2 O-O-O 16. Bg5 f6 17. Rad1 Nd5 18. Be3 Bd6 19. Rxd5 Bxh2+ 20. Kxh2 Qxd5 21. Bxa7) 15. Qe2 { [%eval -5.32] } (15. Qf3?? { Blunder. Best move was Qe2. } { (-1.53 → -5.23) Blunder. Best move was Qe2. } { Leaves the Bd2 hanging, essentially losing the game. } 15... Qxd2 16. Qxb7 (16. Rad1 Qb4 (16... Qa5?? { Blunder. Best move was Qb4. } { (-6.30 → 3.57) Blunder. Best move was Qb4. } 17. Qxb7 f5 (17... Rd8?? { Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was f5. } { (3.40 → Mate in 2) Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was f5. } 18. Qc6+ { Black resigns. }) 18. b4 Qa4 19. Qxa8+ Kf7 20. Qb7 h6 21. Rd7 Qxa2 22. Rdxe7+ Bxe7 23. Rxe7+ Kf6 24. h4) 17. Qd5) 16... Rd8 17. Qb5+ Qd7) 15... O-O-O { [%eval -5.18] } 1-0


