{ After 31...Be8, White's best move in the position leads to a mating sequence: can you find it on your own?

In this recent correspondence game against a much higher rated opponent, I am White and my much higher rated opponent's queenside manoeuvres let me grasp the initiative for a few consecutive moves, setting up a powerful attack against him while he realizes to his astonishment the tables have turned! In this position, his queenside pieces cannot contribute to his king's precarious defense. So, despite my opponent having achieved what appeared to the both of us as a crushing material and positional advantage only a few moves ago, his b and c pawns beeing completely unopposed and seemingly destined to one or the other's inevitable promotion, Black now finds himself in serious difficulty. Neither of us would have believed this possible only a few moves before. }
 *


